{
  "text": "Increasing the employment of persons with disabilities is associated with both extrinsic economic rewards and intrinsic rewards, such as greater quality of life and greater physical and psychological well-being [CITATION_1] . The findings of our previous research confirmed that mobility impaired individuals with higher educational level reported less internalized anger and externalized hostility compared to individuals with lower educational level. In addition, employed individuals expressed less depression and internalized anger and greater adjustment than unemployed individuals .",
